body:
Fixes #30

Don't know why, but
```
touch qq
ln -s qq qq2
rm qq
ln -s qq2 qq
```
shows that links points to non existent file instead infinite recursion

title: Add support for symbolic links
body:
Fixes #80

To use it, at least 2 elements from same category must be selected and clicking at symlnk button will remove second and later elements and simlinks with same name will be created which will point at first file.

title: Remove orbtk frontend
body:
Orbtk frontend was never finished, due to Intelij Idea bugs.

But a lot of things like missing file chooser or advanced GUI elements like TreeViews etc. probably in future would cause many problems.

For this reason, I decided to focus entirely on improving GTK frontend.

body:
Fixes #112

I don't know if there is too much sense in creating advanced algorithms to select elements, because there is a vast array of possible selection options and the big amount of edgy situations.

I think that simple selection of the longest names is good enough.
